'''Diplomatic pouches''' were small cases used by dignitaries to carry sensitive, valuable, weapons, or even illegal items. They were immune to searches by most security forces and checkpoints. Many diplomatic pouches contained explosive devices which were activated by unauthorized attempt at access.

